It should say 'fascism', not 'fascist'.

'Civic nationalism' is just a way making 'nationalism' sound better, but actually doesn't give any meaning.  Also, the Scottish National Party genuinely has fascist roots and they display evidence of Anglophobia, claiming that they are somehow oppressed.
'Civic' is not a meaningful term.  SNP are just nationalist.  'Scottish nationalism' is enough to describe the SNP.
